# Tech stack & dependencies (project defaults)

Use these technologies by default when designing or implementing features in this repo. Avoid introducing alternatives unless explicitly requested.

## Platform & core stack

- Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS (+ `shadcn/ui` for UI components)
- pnpm (package manager)

## Azure DevOps integration

- Use the **official SDK**: `azure-devops-node-api` for PR metadata and creating comment threads.

## Diff generation (source of truth)

- Generate diffs locally with `git` (clone/fetch + `git diff ...`) and execute CLIs using `execa`.
- Parse unified diffs with `parse-diff` (or an equivalent diff parser).

## AI engines (pluggable)

- **CodeRabbit CLI**: general quality review (run via `execa`).
- **Claude Code CLI**: rule-compliance review (run via `execa` in headless mode).
- Both run **in parallel** by default. Output validated with Zod.

## Forms, validation, rendering

- Validation: `zod`
- Forms: `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers`
- Markdown rendering: `react-markdown`

## Persistence (local-first)

- Prisma: `prisma` + `@prisma/client`
- SQLite

## Observability & quality

- Logging: `pino`
- Formatting: `prettier` (+ `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss`)
